00:11:33,376 --> 00:11:36,060
Delaying his tumor resection is
just gonna worsen his prognosis.

253
00:11:36,095 --> 00:11:38,229
But if there<i> is</i>
something else going on,

254
00:11:38,264 --> 00:11:41,098
it would increase his risk for
perioperative complications.

255
00:11:41,134 --> 00:11:42,762
Yeah, okay. Yeah,
fine. Run your tests.

256
00:11:42,786 --> 00:11:44,997
But I'm not gonna postpone
the surgery much longer.

257
00:11:45,021 --> 00:11:47,405
Well, barring any issues,
we'll still get it done today.

258
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:48,839
Okay.

259
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:50,742
How's Henry?

260
00:11:50,777 --> 00:11:52,526
Uh, well, his...

261
00:11:52,579 --> 00:11:55,174
heart's not stopping anymore.

262
00:11:55,198 --> 00:11:57,548
But he has a long road ahead.

263
00:11:57,584 --> 00:12:00,401
It happened
because you told Zoey

264
00:12:00,454 --> 00:12:02,336
the VNS was safe when it wasn't.

265
00:12:02,372 --> 00:12:04,517
You put profits
over patients, again.

266
00:12:04,541 --> 00:12:07,108
I pulled all QuoVadis
devices as soon as I learned

267
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:08,855
the VNS was flawed.

268
00:12:08,879 --> 00:12:10,728
Good for you. But Gordon Page

269
00:12:10,763 --> 00:12:13,280
is still putting patients at
risk, now more than ever,

270
00:12:13,316 --> 00:12:14,916
actually.

271
00:12:14,951 --> 00:12:18,052
I've done everything
I can to stop him,

272
00:12:18,087 --> 00:12:20,921
and you have no idea
what I've sacrificed

273
00:12:20,957 --> 00:12:22,701
to protect patients
from this man.

274
00:12:22,725 --> 00:12:24,074
He's coming for me next.

275
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:27,312
So you save your
morality lesson.

276
00:12:39,409 --> 00:12:41,626
I'll let you take that.

277
00:12:45,165 --> 00:12:46,809
Feeling a bit better?

278
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:49,050
Yeah, thanks to your drugs.

279
00:12:49,085 --> 00:12:50,718
Are you single, honey?

280
00:12:50,753 --> 00:12:52,887
Kay's got a boyfriend,
but it isn't serious.

281
00:12:52,923 --> 00:12:54,939
- Ma,<i> quit.</i>
- Oh, you can fuss

282
00:12:54,975 --> 00:12:58,393
over me, but I don't get
to be involved in your life?

283
00:12:58,428 --> 00:13:00,311
I see gallstones.

284
00:13:00,346 --> 00:13:01,790
But there's no
gallbladder wall thickening.

285
00:13:01,814 --> 00:13:04,649
You're right, no sign
of acute cholecystitis.

286
00:13:04,684 --> 00:13:06,116
That's a good thing?

287
00:13:06,153 --> 00:13:07,751
Yes and no.

288
00:13:07,787 --> 00:13:09,749
We've controlled
your flare-up today,

289
00:13:09,773 --> 00:13:12,323
but I think you'll need surgery
soon to remove your gallbladder.

290
00:13:12,359 --> 00:13:14,286
Well, let's do it
now, get it over with.

291
00:13:14,310 --> 00:13:15,938
I can't take this
pain much longer.

292
00:13:15,962 --> 00:13:17,929
That won't actually
be possible here.

293
00:13:17,964 --> 00:13:20,832
You don't have insurance, and
Chastain is a private hospital.

294
00:13:20,867 --> 00:13:22,311
They're not gonna
do that surgery

295
00:13:22,335 --> 00:13:23,763
unless your situation
is life-threatening.

296
00:13:23,787 --> 00:13:26,353
So I got to be dying
to get some help?

297
00:13:26,389 --> 00:13:28,989
Well, who the hell
made these rules?

298
00:13:29,042 --> 00:13:31,103
Well, we could refer you to
County to get it scheduled.

299
00:13:31,127 --> 00:13:32,793
They take uninsured patients.

300
00:13:32,846 --> 00:13:34,857
Typically, their wait
list is months long.

301
00:13:34,881 --> 00:13:37,265
Well, we can't wait here. Uh-uh.

302
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:39,100
We got no place to stay.

303
00:13:39,135 --> 00:13:41,436
- We're gonna have to go home.
- You'd make her go home

304
00:13:41,471 --> 00:13:43,605
and suffer like this,
for months, maybe?

305
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:45,016
And what if she
suddenly gets worse?

306
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:46,785
You know what? I
have a friend at County.

307
00:13:46,809 --> 00:13:49,343
Let me reach out, see if
they can get her in right now.

308
00:13:49,396 --> 00:13:52,196
- All right, then.
- Thank you.

309
00:13:54,184 --> 00:13:56,796
<i>You know, Bell
told me about you.</i>

310
00:13:56,820 --> 00:13:59,386
He said you are one
real pain in the ass.

311
00:13:59,421 --> 00:14:01,789
I'll take it. Pain-in-the-ass
people get things done.

312
00:14:03,860 --> 00:14:05,793
You know...

313
00:14:05,828 --> 00:14:08,813
when Randolph was
young, he was a lot like you.

314
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:12,317
I remember his second
year as a resident.

315
00:14:12,352 --> 00:14:14,501
He got into a real
shouting match

316
00:14:14,554 --> 00:14:16,638
with his chief of surgery.

317
00:14:16,673 --> 00:14:19,690
He wanted to stop doctors
from smoking in the hospitals.

318
00:14:19,725 --> 00:14:22,677
Said it was no good
for anyone's health,

319
00:14:22,712 --> 00:14:24,495
patients<i> or</i> doctors.

320
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:27,197
Everyone, they just
thought he was no fun.

321
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:29,600
But... he was right.

322
00:14:29,635 --> 00:14:32,537
And eventually,
they banned smoking.

323
00:14:32,572 --> 00:14:35,156
And the very next year...

324
00:14:35,191 --> 00:14:37,391
- he helped me quit.
- Oh, Bell,

325
00:14:37,444 --> 00:14:39,326
a reformer?

326
00:14:39,361 --> 00:14:41,362
That's hard to believe.

327
00:14:41,414 --> 00:14:44,249
This place has a way
of changing people.

328
00:14:44,284 --> 00:14:46,166
Just wait.

329
00:14:46,202 --> 00:14:48,285
Change you, too.

330
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:03,250
Hey.

331
00:15:03,285 --> 00:15:05,269
- Hey.
- You need anything?

332
00:15:05,304 --> 00:15:07,271
- No.
- You ready?

333
00:15:07,307 --> 00:15:09,089
Yes. I want to do this.

334
00:15:09,124 --> 00:15:11,108
Yeah, you're gonna be great.

335
00:15:11,143 --> 00:15:14,212
We'll be all set for you in
about ten minutes, Ms. Barnett.

336
00:15:14,247 --> 00:15:15,446
Thanks.

337
00:15:17,266 --> 00:15:19,094
I'll be with Henry
until they need me.

338
00:15:19,118 --> 00:15:21,736
Yeah. Go.

339
00:15:21,771 --> 00:15:23,665
<i>W-What's your
favorite kind of game?</i>

340
00:15:23,689 --> 00:15:25,551
<i>On the story mode games,</i>

341
00:15:25,575 --> 00:15:27,436
there's a bad guy
that you have to stop

342
00:15:27,460 --> 00:15:29,055
with missions that connect

343
00:15:29,079 --> 00:15:30,606
- to each other.
- Oh.

344
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:31,940
And it's really cool.

345
00:15:31,964 --> 00:15:33,559
Ooh. So you're hunting bad guys.

346
00:15:33,583 --> 00:15:35,983
- What are you doing here?
- Ms. Barnett.

347
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:38,286
I came here to check
in on you and Henry.

348
00:15:40,307 --> 00:15:43,007
Mom, he gave it to me.

349
00:15:43,042 --> 00:15:44,287
Look, I understand
that you're upset.

350
00:15:44,311 --> 00:15:47,011
I am, too. That's
why I'm here... to help.

351
00:15:48,348 --> 00:15:50,113
Hey.

352
00:15:50,149 --> 00:15:51,949
I was just coming to check in.

353
00:15:51,985 --> 00:15:53,601
What's going on?

354
00:15:53,653 --> 00:15:56,037
Mr. Page was just leaving.

355
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:06,413
You all right?

356
00:16:06,449 --> 00:16:07,681
Yes.

357
00:16:08,951 --> 00:16:10,918
Well, they're ready for you.

358
00:16:10,953 --> 00:16:13,003
I'll stay with Henry.

359
00:16:13,039 --> 00:16:14,371
Thanks, Nic.

360
00:16:22,048 --> 00:16:24,816
Hear me out. Henry had
a very rare adverse event.

361
00:16:24,851 --> 00:16:26,946
Is that what you call it?

362
00:16:26,970 --> 00:16:29,887
Every new lifesaving device
has glitches in the first few years,

363
00:16:29,922 --> 00:16:32,451
and then we adjust and we learn.

364
00:16:32,475 --> 00:16:34,692
He's going to Duke.
They'll help him.

365
00:16:34,727 --> 00:16:36,377
Now, please leave us alone.

366
00:16:36,412 --> 00:16:38,390
And who's paying for
his treatment at Duke?

367
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:41,281
If the surgery is experimental,
insurance won't cover it.

368
00:16:41,317 --> 00:16:42,894
Will you be able
to keep your job

369
00:16:42,918 --> 00:16:44,513
while you're with your
son in North Carolina?

370
00:16:44,537 --> 00:16:46,777
Without a job, will you
even have health insurance?

371
00:16:48,223 --> 00:16:50,369
- What do you want?
- Henry's condition
is likely permanent.

372
00:16:50,393 --> 00:16:52,559
I'm here to tell you
that QuoVadis is willing

373
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:54,211
to cover all his
medical bills...

374
00:16:54,246 --> 00:16:56,041
Not for a month,
not for a year...

375
00:16:56,065 --> 00:16:58,265
For his whole life.

376
00:17:01,103 --> 00:17:02,920
I don't believe you.

377
00:17:02,955 --> 00:17:05,556
I'll put it in writing.

378
00:17:05,591 --> 00:17:08,559
It's the least we can do.

379
00:17:12,047 --> 00:17:14,832
And in return, I'm guessing...

380
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:17,034
you don't want me
to go talk to the press.

381
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,238
Don't make me your enemy.

382
00:17:22,441 --> 00:17:24,158
Take the offer.

383
00:17:24,193 --> 00:17:27,394
And if you go public with a
grievance against QuoVadis,

384
00:17:27,429 --> 00:17:29,997
now or ever...

385
00:17:30,032 --> 00:17:32,199
this deal goes away.

386
00:17:34,036 --> 00:17:36,437
We're ready for you
now, Ms. Barnett.

387
00:17:50,753 --> 00:17:52,319
How much?

388
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:55,055
How much was Page's offer?

389
00:17:55,091 --> 00:17:57,036
I heard he was here.

390
00:17:57,060 --> 00:17:59,727
There were more zeroes than
I've ever seen in one number.

391
00:17:59,762 --> 00:18:01,195
You can't take it.

392
00:18:01,231 --> 00:18:02,863
We'll find another way

393
00:18:02,898 --> 00:18:04,927
to pay for Henry's
treatment, I promise you.

394
00:18:04,951 --> 00:18:07,034
- You can't promise that.
- Yes, I can.

395
00:18:07,069 --> 00:18:09,470
I<i> do</i> promise that. Zoey,
you need to speak out,

396
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:11,322
or people will die if you don't.

397
00:18:11,357 --> 00:18:14,274
I get it, I get it... that kind
of money, it is tempting.

398
00:18:14,327 --> 00:18:16,221
Even all that money,
it can't be enough

399
00:18:16,245 --> 00:18:18,245
to stop me from
waking up every night

400
00:18:18,298 --> 00:18:20,058
and running into Henry's
room to make sure

401
00:18:20,082 --> 00:18:23,100
he didn't stop
breathing. It won't...

402
00:18:26,756 --> 00:18:29,156
It won't bring his brother back.

403
00:18:32,928 --> 00:18:35,429
I signed already.

404
00:18:35,482 --> 00:18:38,265
QuoVadis wired the money.

405
00:18:39,519 --> 00:18:42,052
It's done.

406
00:18:42,939 --> 00:18:45,055
I am not a horrible person.

407
00:18:47,042 --> 00:18:49,310
I will help arrange...

408
00:18:49,345 --> 00:18:52,113
for Henry's transfer to Duke.

409
00:18:53,549 --> 00:18:56,784
We need to get him
there as quickly as we can.

410
00:18:56,819 --> 00:18:59,153
Thank you, Conrad.

411
00:18:59,188 --> 00:19:01,471
For everything.

412
00:19:04,076 --> 00:19:05,359
Good luck, Zoey.

413
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:15,452
What about cancellations?

414
00:19:15,488 --> 00:19:18,806
There's got to be
some way to get her in.

415
00:19:18,841 --> 00:19:20,191
Okay, thanks, man.

416
00:19:20,226 --> 00:19:22,693
Nope. I understand.

417
00:19:22,729 --> 00:19:24,673
They wanted to
schedule Marilyn's surgery

418
00:19:24,697 --> 00:19:25,679
seven weeks out.

419
00:19:25,714 --> 00:19:27,147
I talked them down to three.

420
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:29,684
- This isn't your fault.
- No, in a way, it is.

421
00:19:29,736 --> 00:19:32,904
The mobile clinic helped me
stop crises before they happened.

422
00:19:32,939 --> 00:19:34,382
I am sure that you
encouraged Marilyn

423
00:19:34,406 --> 00:19:35,884
to live a healthier
lifestyle many times.

424
00:19:35,908 --> 00:19:38,137
I mean, there's only
so much we can do.

425
00:19:38,161 --> 00:19:40,878
This is the situation, so
we have to deal with it.

426
00:19:42,348 --> 00:19:44,097
Okay, how?

427
00:19:45,952 --> 00:19:47,417
Where's your RV?

428
00:19:47,453 --> 00:19:49,315
- It's down the street.
- Pull it around.

429
00:19:49,339 --> 00:19:51,259
We're gonna have
a working lunch.

430
00:19:54,761 --> 00:19:57,561
Welcome to Le Château Shaw.

431
00:19:57,596 --> 00:19:59,379
- Château what?
- Come on.

432
00:19:59,432 --> 00:20:01,160
You're mere steps from
the best medical care

433
00:20:01,184 --> 00:20:03,162
Atlanta has to offer.

434
00:20:03,186 --> 00:20:05,369
What on earth...?

435
00:20:06,806 --> 00:20:08,723
- Oh, my.
- We provide our guests

436
00:20:08,775 --> 00:20:12,225
with the utmost privacy.

437
00:20:12,278 --> 00:20:15,429
Unfortunately, the pool's
closed for renovation indefinitely.

438
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:18,510
- Are you sure this is okay? It should
be fine until your mom has the surgery.

439
00:20:18,534 --> 00:20:21,046
- And there's a supermarket within
walking distance. Yeah. And there's

440
00:20:21,070 --> 00:20:23,298
a kitchen in the clinic...
Use it anytime you need.

441
00:20:23,322 --> 00:20:24,571
But...

442
00:20:24,606 --> 00:20:26,456
no more fatty foods.

443
00:20:26,492 --> 00:20:28,053
They'll only worsen
your gallbladder attacks.

444
00:20:28,077 --> 00:20:30,610
Listen to Dr. Shaw on
this. It's very important.

445
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:32,107
No more peanut butter.

446
00:20:32,131 --> 00:20:34,193
No fried chicken.

447
00:20:34,217 --> 00:20:36,566
No chocolate, no dairy.

448
00:20:36,603 --> 00:20:38,552
And... definitely no more bacon.

449
00:20:38,605 --> 00:20:40,583
- Well, then what's left?
- Fruits,

450
00:20:40,607 --> 00:20:42,567
veggies, whole
grains, lean protein.

451
00:20:44,510 --> 00:20:47,228
No bacon? Harsh.

452
00:20:50,617 --> 00:20:52,261
Mina said you're
storming the castle.

453
00:20:52,285 --> 00:20:54,101
We're going.

454
00:20:54,137 --> 00:20:56,453
Bradley's dead.
Julian is still missing.

455
00:20:56,489 --> 00:20:58,066
I'm not gonna just sit
around while Gordon

456
00:20:58,090 --> 00:20:59,485
- keeps hurting patients.
- His Innovation Summit

457
00:20:59,509 --> 00:21:01,629
is open to the public...
We can walk right in.

458
00:21:01,660 --> 00:21:03,110
We need to get the truth

459
00:21:03,145 --> 00:21:04,640
about the VNS to the
military leaders there

460
00:21:04,664 --> 00:21:06,058
who can actually
stop this thing.

461
00:21:06,082 --> 00:21:08,616
Wow. Leaking what
the VNS did to Henry...

462
00:21:08,651 --> 00:21:11,218
Now, that would be
a violation of HIPAA.

463
00:21:11,254 --> 00:21:13,304
Which is why we're removing

464
00:21:13,339 --> 00:21:15,579
anything that would
reveal the patient's identity.

465
00:21:19,378 --> 00:21:20,644
Go get 'em.

466
00:21:29,822 --> 00:21:32,523
One of my investigators
was able to locate

467
00:21:32,558 --> 00:21:34,458
a former QuoVadis employee

468
00:21:34,493 --> 00:21:36,494
who witnessed
fraud at the company.

469
00:21:36,529 --> 00:21:38,841
- Will they come forward?
- No, they're afraid of Gordon.

470
00:21:38,865 --> 00:21:40,825
So we'll have to
find proof ourselves.

471
00:21:40,849 --> 00:21:42,833
What proof?

472
00:21:42,868 --> 00:21:44,318
Zoey's out.

473
00:21:44,353 --> 00:21:46,198
The VNS surgeries
are in a few hours.

474
00:21:46,222 --> 00:21:48,205
- We're running out of time.
- I know.

475
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:50,185
I figured you'd be halfway
to QuoVadis by now.

476
00:21:50,209 --> 00:21:53,209
I can't leave. I got
critical patients.

477
00:21:54,297 --> 00:21:56,496
There's one now.

478
00:21:56,532 --> 00:21:57,998
I got to go.

479
00:22:00,135 --> 00:22:01,529
He's not responding
to fluid boluses.

480
00:22:01,553 --> 00:22:02,619
Still hypotensive.

481
00:22:02,655 --> 00:22:04,021
You thinking cardiogenic shock?

482
00:22:04,056 --> 00:22:05,272
He's vasodilated.

483
00:22:05,308 --> 00:22:06,940
His fever just spiked to 103.

484
00:22:06,976 --> 00:22:08,308
This is septic shock.

485
00:22:08,344 --> 00:22:10,424
Draw a lactate, set
up for a central line.

486
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:13,280
We've already
got blood cultures.

487
00:22:13,315 --> 00:22:15,460
Let's get him started on
vancomycin and cefepime.

488
00:22:15,484 --> 00:22:17,529
Hang norepinephrine
and titrate to a MAP of 65.

489
00:22:17,553 --> 00:22:18,619
Stay with us, buddy.

490
00:22:20,239 --> 00:22:22,606
I'm seeing Osler's nodes.

491
00:22:29,248 --> 00:22:31,326
Those splinter hemorrhages
weren't there two minutes ago.

492
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:32,883
Cardiac mass must be infected.

493
00:22:32,919 --> 00:22:34,318
It's not just a myxoma.

494
00:22:34,353 --> 00:22:36,253
He's got endocarditis as well.

495
00:22:36,288 --> 00:22:38,817
I've only seen two patients
with both in my entire career.

496
00:22:38,841 --> 00:22:40,891
And did they survive?

497
00:22:40,926 --> 00:22:42,025
One did.

498
00:22:47,350 --> 00:22:49,344
Well, at least his pressures
are starting to come back up.

499
00:22:49,368 --> 00:22:51,418
Obviously, under
normal circumstances,

500
00:22:51,454 --> 00:22:53,081
we would recommend
holding off on surgery

501
00:22:53,105 --> 00:22:54,688
with such a recent infection.

502
00:22:54,723 --> 00:22:57,369
But with Simon's
valve deteriorating -

503
00:22:57,393 --> 00:23:00,343
and his heart failure
worsening, he needs it soon.

504
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:02,513
His surgery just got
a whole lot riskier.

505
00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:05,348
Let's broaden his antibiotics to
cover any possible resistance.

506
00:23:05,384 --> 00:23:08,068
Do we still go forward?

507
00:23:08,121 --> 00:23:10,537
If he does nothing, he'll live

508
00:23:10,573 --> 00:23:12,434
for a couple more
months. Operating under

509
00:23:12,458 --> 00:23:15,426
these circumstances might
mean he never wakes up.

510
00:23:18,063 --> 00:23:20,748
I'll talk to him.

511
00:23:20,783 --> 00:23:23,384
It's his decision.

512
00:23:29,008 --> 00:23:31,474
This was all they had left.

513
00:23:31,510 --> 00:23:33,227
Apparently, the word is out.

514
00:23:33,262 --> 00:23:34,912
You know, if I got sick,

515
00:23:34,947 --> 00:23:37,531
half this hospital would
pop a bottle of champagne.

516
00:23:37,567 --> 00:23:40,967
Why? The other half don't drink?

517
00:23:41,003 --> 00:23:42,152
Okay.

518
00:23:42,188 --> 00:23:44,454
So, how bad is it?

519
00:23:46,175 --> 00:23:48,459
Surgery's risky.

520
00:23:48,494 --> 00:23:51,879
Even in Austin's hands, uh...

521
00:23:51,914 --> 00:23:54,798
the odds of
survival aren't great.

522
00:23:56,586 --> 00:23:59,903
What happens if AJ doesn't
cut this thing out of me?

523
00:23:59,939 --> 00:24:01,154
What then?

524
00:24:03,342 --> 00:24:06,960
Then the tumor will
completely obstruct your heart,

525
00:24:07,013 --> 00:24:08,962
and...

526
00:24:08,997 --> 00:24:10,780
you'll have a month,

527
00:24:10,817 --> 00:24:13,183
maybe two.

528
00:24:13,219 --> 00:24:16,436
Get your affairs in order.

529
00:24:16,489 --> 00:24:20,191
So my choices are
risking dying on the table

530
00:24:20,226 --> 00:24:21,292
or...

531
00:24:21,327 --> 00:24:23,544
start saying goodbye.

532
00:24:25,464 --> 00:24:27,181
Yeah, I'm afraid so.

533
00:24:30,986 --> 00:24:34,555
Want to take a day
and-and think about it?

534
00:24:35,575 --> 00:24:37,541
I'm a betting man.

535
00:24:37,576 --> 00:24:39,959
I've beaten long odds before.

536
00:24:39,995 --> 00:24:42,362
Nah...

537
00:24:42,398 --> 00:24:44,531
let's do it.

538
00:24:45,584 --> 00:24:47,851
All right.

539
00:24:48,871 --> 00:24:51,304
All right.

540
00:24:53,892 --> 00:24:55,509
You know,

541
00:24:55,544 --> 00:24:57,144
I love my job.

542
00:24:57,179 --> 00:24:59,613
Pay's not great.

543
00:25:01,067 --> 00:25:03,016
But every day, I...

544
00:25:03,051 --> 00:25:05,552
get to help you save lives.

545
00:25:05,588 --> 00:25:08,455
And I sleep like a baby.

546
00:25:08,491 --> 00:25:11,541
Oh, it's been a while since
I slept through the night.

547
00:25:12,561 --> 00:25:15,545
You love this place
as much as I do.

548
00:25:15,580 --> 00:25:18,998
I know you'll do
whatever you have to

549
00:25:19,051 --> 00:25:21,334
to make things right.

550
00:25:23,889 --> 00:25:25,438
Hey.

551
00:25:28,043 --> 00:25:30,394
You better get ready.

552
00:25:34,749 --> 00:25:36,483
The VNS stopped

553
00:25:36,518 --> 00:25:38,096
the patient's heart
every three minutes.

554
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:39,436
It's a miracle he survived.

555
00:25:39,471 --> 00:25:41,088
It nearly killed him.

556
00:25:41,123 --> 00:25:42,606
If you move forward with this,

557
00:25:42,641 --> 00:25:45,542
you are putting a ticking time
bomb in every one of these vets.

558
00:25:45,577 --> 00:25:46,955
I'm sorry, wh-who are you again?

559
00:25:46,979 --> 00:25:49,446
We're doctors who
work at Chastain.

560
00:25:49,482 --> 00:25:51,615
The device is FDA-approved.

561
00:25:51,650 --> 00:25:53,728
But the FDA doesn't
do independent testing.

562
00:25:53,752 --> 00:25:55,714
And they're notorious
for grandfathering devices

563
00:25:55,738 --> 00:25:58,154
based on previous ones
that don't even work.

564
00:26:00,042 --> 00:26:02,759
We're satisfied
with the trial data

565
00:26:02,795 --> 00:26:05,446
Gordon Page provided us.

566
00:26:11,620 --> 00:26:13,203
Look.

567
00:26:13,238 --> 00:26:15,188
That's Raptor's mentor...

568
00:26:15,224 --> 00:26:18,708
The one that recommended
the heart valve that killed Bradley.

569
00:26:18,743 --> 00:26:21,611
I don't suppose punching him
would do us any good, would it?

570
00:26:21,646 --> 00:26:23,313
Come on.

571
00:26:23,348 --> 00:26:25,793
<i>May I have your
attention, please.</i>

572
00:26:25,817 --> 00:26:30,070
<i>Our presentation will begin
shortly in the main lobby.</i>

573
00:26:30,122 --> 00:26:32,773
Dr. Benedict, I'm Dr. Okafor.

574
00:26:32,808 --> 00:26:34,875
I met you with Dr. Austin.

575
00:26:34,910 --> 00:26:36,960
Yeah, who could forget?

576
00:26:36,996 --> 00:26:39,730
We're here because Gordon's
VNS is as deadly as his heart valve.

577
00:26:39,765 --> 00:26:41,393
And it's about to
endanger dozens of lives

578
00:26:41,417 --> 00:26:43,300
if we don't stop it.

579
00:26:45,704 --> 00:26:48,088
Give AJ my best.

580
00:26:48,140 --> 00:26:52,476
Dr. Benedict, you still
have a reputation to protect.

581
00:26:52,511 --> 00:26:54,351
If you know anything... No, no.

582
00:26:54,380 --> 00:26:56,680
The greatest
betrayal of Austin's life

583
00:26:56,715 --> 00:26:58,693
was when his birth
parents abandoned him,

584
00:26:58,717 --> 00:27:01,268
throwing him away like trash.

585
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,437
You were a close second.

586
00:27:03,472 --> 00:27:05,672
That's how much your
friendship meant to him.

587
00:27:05,708 --> 00:27:07,774
That's how much he trusted you.

588
00:27:07,809 --> 00:27:10,461
The man you used to be

589
00:27:10,496 --> 00:27:13,130
and the one you can be again.

590
00:27:13,165 --> 00:27:15,132
When Mina said
the VNS will fail,

591
00:27:15,167 --> 00:27:16,967
you weren't surprised. Why?

592
00:27:18,570 --> 00:27:20,304
I didn't have a choice.

593
00:27:20,339 --> 00:27:22,706
We had to get the
device to market.

594
00:27:22,741 --> 00:27:23,790
You and Gordon?

595
00:27:23,843 --> 00:27:25,959
I swear...

596
00:27:25,994 --> 00:27:28,662
- I didn't know at first.
- Know what?

597
00:27:40,592 --> 00:27:42,042
Let's take a walk.

598
00:27:54,890 --> 00:27:58,124
Your pre-op numbers look
quite reassuring, my brother.

599
00:27:58,159 --> 00:27:59,692
Once that tumor's removed,

600
00:27:59,745 --> 00:28:01,523
we'll see about finding
you that Rockette.

601
00:28:03,182 --> 00:28:06,649
Ah, I thought I'd seen
this room from every angle.

602
00:28:06,685 --> 00:28:10,554
But I've never
seen it like this.

603
00:28:12,057 --> 00:28:13,924
Okay, transfer on three.

604
00:28:13,959 --> 00:28:16,376
One, two, three.

605
00:28:20,349 --> 00:28:22,966
Starting the propofol.

606
00:28:23,953 --> 00:28:25,351
Randolph.

607
00:28:25,387 --> 00:28:26,764
Yeah?

608
00:28:26,788 --> 00:28:29,122
Try not to make a mess.

609
00:28:42,721 --> 00:28:45,021
She's on the floor.

610
00:28:45,056 --> 00:28:46,957
It looks real bad.

611
00:28:49,495 --> 00:28:52,012
- The pain usually goes away.
- And it's gotten worse.

612
00:28:54,834 --> 00:28:56,683
We need to get her to Chastain.

613
00:28:56,718 --> 00:29:00,103
Marilyn, one of your gallstones
is now causing an infection.

614
00:29:00,138 --> 00:29:01,899
It's a good thing you didn't
head back to Alabama.

615
00:29:01,923 --> 00:29:03,752
This could've happened on
the road, with nowhere to go.

616
00:29:03,776 --> 00:29:05,703
Ultrasound shows
pericholecystic fluid.

617
00:29:05,727 --> 00:29:08,095
And her white count
is at 20,000. No fever.

618
00:29:08,147 --> 00:29:10,530
I'm Dr. Nolan. I'll be removing
your gallbladder today.

619
00:29:10,566 --> 00:29:12,043
Oh, hallelujah.

620
00:29:12,067 --> 00:29:13,366
Don't usually get that reaction.

621
00:29:13,401 --> 00:29:14,701
You can take it out now?

622
00:29:14,736 --> 00:29:15,902
Now it's an emergency.

623
00:29:15,938 --> 00:29:17,132
Get her prepped for surgery.

624
00:29:17,156 --> 00:29:18,588
I'll see you in the OR, okay?

625
00:29:21,961 --> 00:29:24,878
I can't thank you enough.

626
00:29:24,914 --> 00:29:26,729
Whatever you've done,

627
00:29:26,765 --> 00:29:28,510
it is not too late
to make it right.

628
00:29:28,534 --> 00:29:29,594
- Talk to us.
- What do you know?

629
00:29:29,618 --> 00:29:30,767
What has QuoVadis done?

630
00:29:30,803 --> 00:29:32,085
How can we stop this?

631
00:29:38,493 --> 00:29:40,594
Oh...

632
00:29:44,783 --> 00:29:47,083
I want to talk to AJ.

633
00:29:47,118 --> 00:29:48,735
He deserves the truth.

634
00:29:48,770 --> 00:29:50,971
Just him, not you.

635
00:29:52,324 --> 00:29:54,691
All right.

636
00:30:14,346 --> 00:30:18,665
<i>Here we have the QuoVadis
vagus nerve stimulator.</i>

637
00:30:18,700 --> 00:30:21,284
<i>All cities are online.</i>

638
00:30:21,319 --> 00:30:24,950
<i>The surgeries
are about to begin.</i>

639
00:30:24,974 --> 00:30:28,307
<i>Dr. Stevenson presiding.</i>

640
00:30:33,699 --> 00:30:36,483
The patient is David Jones.

641
00:30:36,518 --> 00:30:39,069
Date of birth 8/6/1989.

642
00:30:39,104 --> 00:30:41,721
<i>Procedure to be performed
is surgical implantation</i>

643
00:30:41,757 --> 00:30:44,490
<i>of a vagus nerve stimulator.</i>

644
00:30:44,543 --> 00:30:46,910
Let's begin. 10 blade.

645
00:30:51,383 --> 00:30:53,733
<i>I can't reach Austin.</i>

646
00:30:53,769 --> 00:30:55,101
I've called three times.

647
00:30:56,855 --> 00:30:58,555
He's in surgery.

648
00:30:58,590 --> 00:30:59,756
What is going on?

649
00:30:59,792 --> 00:31:00,757
Abe doesn't trust us.

650
00:31:00,792 --> 00:31:01,920
He'll only talk to Austin.

651
00:31:01,944 --> 00:31:04,044
He knows something
that can help.

652
00:31:04,079 --> 00:31:06,513
I'm on it.

653
00:31:15,608 --> 00:31:18,241
All right, let's start
rewarming Simon

654
00:31:18,276 --> 00:31:20,160
and get his heart pumping again.

655
00:31:20,195 --> 00:31:21,456
Defib paddles to me.

656
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:23,274
Charge to ten joules.

657
00:31:24,617 --> 00:31:26,599
Clear.

658
00:31:33,042 --> 00:31:35,854
He's in V-fib.

659
00:31:35,878 --> 00:31:37,911
Give 300 of amio and try again.

660
00:31:50,409 --> 00:31:52,909
I'm here. I'm here.

661
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:56,323
And clear.

662
00:32:02,104 --> 00:32:04,570
He won't stay out of V-fib.

663
00:32:04,623 --> 00:32:06,573
His electrolytes are normal.

664
00:32:06,608 --> 00:32:08,436
I've given him more magnesium,
but it's not doing anything.

665
00:32:08,460 --> 00:32:09,793
Get the intracardiac epi ready.

666
00:32:09,828 --> 00:32:11,939
Just worried his heart
sustained too much damage

667
00:32:11,963 --> 00:32:13,079
during the procedure.

668
00:32:15,350 --> 00:32:16,950
Injecting one milligram

669
00:32:16,985 --> 00:32:19,898
of epi.

670
00:32:36,221 --> 00:32:37,637
I can't get to him.

671
00:32:38,657 --> 00:32:40,740
You have to.

672
00:32:40,776 --> 00:32:43,125
I can't. His patient could die.

673
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:50,200
Let's get him on a balloon pump.

674
00:32:50,235 --> 00:32:51,617
Charge to 20.

675
00:32:51,653 --> 00:32:53,253
Clear.

676
00:32:59,962 --> 00:33:01,940
Come on, Dr. Benedict,

677
00:33:01,964 --> 00:33:03,884
please, tell us
whatever you know.

678
00:33:11,590 --> 00:33:13,924
Where's the balloon pump?!

679
00:33:17,312 --> 00:33:19,062
General?

680
00:33:19,097 --> 00:33:20,847
My name is Marshall Winthrop.

681
00:33:20,882 --> 00:33:23,816
I'm chairman of the board
at Chastain Park Memorial.

682
00:33:23,869 --> 00:33:26,853
We'll be cutting
ties with QuoVadis

683
00:33:26,889 --> 00:33:28,387
because of some information

684
00:33:28,423 --> 00:33:30,463
I thought you'd be
interested in seeing.

685
00:33:31,693 --> 00:33:33,933
Don't you understand
that lives are at stake here?

686
00:33:34,913 --> 00:33:37,080
Please.

687
00:33:37,115 --> 00:33:38,898
- Come on.
- Let's go.

688
00:33:40,519 --> 00:33:42,686
Come on.

689
00:33:52,363 --> 00:33:54,614
Mr. Page wants
to speak with you.

690
00:33:56,602 --> 00:33:58,518
QuoVadis is engaged

691
00:33:58,570 --> 00:34:00,520
in wide-ranging fraud.

692
00:34:00,555 --> 00:34:04,002
All of their devices,
including the VNS,

693
00:34:04,026 --> 00:34:06,159
are being shipped in from China

694
00:34:06,195 --> 00:34:09,695
and then relabeled
as made in the USA.

695
00:34:09,731 --> 00:34:11,380
By law, the military cannot use

696
00:34:11,416 --> 00:34:14,183
any medical device
not American-made.

697
00:34:14,219 --> 00:34:16,097
And those are shipping records

698
00:34:16,121 --> 00:34:18,038
over the last few months.

699
00:34:18,073 --> 00:34:20,657
You have more proof
there than you'll ever need.

700
00:34:44,015 --> 00:34:45,398
What happened?

701
00:34:45,433 --> 00:34:47,901
What happened is the
U.S. military partnered

702
00:34:47,936 --> 00:34:49,619
with a liar and a fraud.

703
00:34:50,656 --> 00:34:53,606
Our contract is
now null and void.

704
00:34:53,641 --> 00:34:56,826
All surgeries are canceled.

705
00:35:36,502 --> 00:35:40,053
Austin said Simon's
heart was too weak.

706
00:35:41,139 --> 00:35:45,225
There is nothing
anyone could have done.

707
00:35:59,140 --> 00:36:01,640
He would have hated this.

708
00:36:28,170 --> 00:36:30,186
♪ ♪

709
00:36:42,550 --> 00:36:45,568
What did you tell them?

710
00:36:46,939 --> 00:36:48,922
I didn't tell them anything.

711
00:36:49,941 --> 00:36:52,458
I wouldn't do that to you.

712
00:36:56,465 --> 00:36:58,731
Good.

713
00:36:58,766 --> 00:37:01,084
I knew I could count on you.

714
00:37:03,071 --> 00:37:06,055
We have some storm clouds ahead.

715
00:37:06,091 --> 00:37:09,542
But we will weather it
if we all stick together.

716
00:37:11,562 --> 00:37:13,563
Talk tomorrow.

