00:37:38,239 --> 00:37:39,823
Yeah, it went great.

719
00:37:39,858 --> 00:37:41,957
Uh, Nolan did it
laparoscopically,

720
00:37:41,993 --> 00:37:43,805
so she and Kay get to
go home in the morning.

721
00:37:43,829 --> 00:37:45,144
Great.

722
00:37:45,180 --> 00:37:46,774
It smells good. What is that?

723
00:37:46,798 --> 00:37:50,133
Eight piece, extra crispy,
with a side of crunchy.

724
00:37:50,168 --> 00:37:52,151
And a milkshake.

725
00:37:54,522 --> 00:37:56,505
Everything we
told her not to eat.

726
00:37:56,541 --> 00:37:57,651
She didn't forget our advice.

727
00:37:57,675 --> 00:37:59,337
She knew exactly
what she was doing.

728
00:37:59,361 --> 00:38:01,461
She just took matters
into her own hands.

729
00:38:02,781 --> 00:38:04,776
She gave herself
a gallbladder attack

730
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:07,617
to get surgery right away.

731
00:38:07,652 --> 00:38:09,612
What's wrong with
a hospital system

732
00:38:09,637 --> 00:38:12,583
when patients have to put
their own lives in jeopardy

733
00:38:12,607 --> 00:38:15,041
just to get access to treatment?

734
00:38:18,130 --> 00:38:20,863
I, uh, was thinking about
what you said earlier.

735
00:38:20,899 --> 00:38:24,500
Made me wonder if
you regret taking this job.

736
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:27,787
Well, it's complicated.

737
00:38:27,822 --> 00:38:29,806
No. I mean, I get it.

738
00:38:29,841 --> 00:38:33,192
We're saving people
from drowning.

739
00:38:33,228 --> 00:38:35,228
You want to teach them to swim.

740
00:38:38,249 --> 00:38:41,134
Look, you got us up and running.

741
00:38:41,186 --> 00:38:43,886
I understand if you want
to go back on the road.

742
00:38:44,890 --> 00:38:46,505
Yeah, you know, I may.

743
00:38:46,540 --> 00:38:48,941
But, uh...

744
00:38:48,977 --> 00:38:52,796
You know why I stay, don't you?

745
00:38:52,831 --> 00:38:54,814
You're here.

746
00:39:00,355 --> 00:39:02,004
We make a great team.

747
00:39:03,858 --> 00:39:05,841
Yes, we do make a great team.

748
00:39:06,861 --> 00:39:10,846
But it feels like maybe
there's something more.

749
00:39:15,337 --> 00:39:17,504
Um, it's late.

750
00:39:17,556 --> 00:39:19,366
I'm gonna take this
stuff home to wash it,

751
00:39:19,390 --> 00:39:22,342
- and I'll see you tomorrow.
- Yeah. Okay.

752
00:39:26,348 --> 00:39:28,347
Good night, Alec.

